### FleetFix Backend — Sample API Requests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Register a dispatcher
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "jane.dispatcher",
  "email": "jane@fleetfix.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123",
  "role": "DISPATCHER"
}

### Sample response
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "User registered successfully",
#   "data": {
#     "userId": 1,
#     "username": "jane.dispatcher",
#     "email": "jane@fleetfix.com",
#     "role": "DISPATCHER",
#     "token": "eyJhbGciOi...",
#     "tokenType": "Bearer"
#   }
# }

### 2. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "jane.dispatcher",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}

### 3. Add a vehicle (requires Bearer token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "registrationNumber": "FL-2026-001",
  "manufacturer": "Ford",
  "model": "Transit",
  "year": 2022,
  "mileage": 34210.5,
  "status": "ACTIVE"
}

### 4. List vehicles (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles?page=0&size=10&sort=registrationNumber,asc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Add a driver
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/drivers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Mike Rodriguez",
  "phone": "+1-555-0199",
  "licenseNumber": "DL-99231"
}

### 6. Assign a vehicle to a driver
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/drivers/1/assign-vehicle
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "vehicleId": 1
}

### 7. Save a GPS coordinate (Tracking module)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tracking/location
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "vehicleId": 1,
  "latitude": 37.7749,
  "longitude": -122.4194,
  "speed": 42.5,
  "heading": 180
}

### 8. Get current vehicle location
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tracking/1/current
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Submit a diagnostic trouble code (DTC) — supplied manually by frontend
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/diagnostics
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "vehicleId": 1,
  "dtcCode": "P0301",
  "description": "Cylinder 1 misfire detected",
  "severity": "HIGH"
}

### 10. Create a repair order
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/repair-orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "vehicleId": 1,
  "diagnosticId": 1,
  "estimatedCompletion": "2026-08-01"
}

### 11. Update repair order status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/repair-orders/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}

### 12. Add a spare part to inventory
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "partNumber": "BRK-PAD-04",
  "partName": "Brake Pad Set",
  "quantity": 50,
  "warehouseLocation": "Aisle 3, Shelf B"
}

### 13. Reserve parts
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory/1/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "quantity": 4
}

### 14. Dashboard stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dashboard/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. Vehicle report
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reports/vehicles
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
